   Philippines. UNHCR helps marginalised indigenous group avoid
       statelessness
       Stories

Ensuring the rights of nomadic seafarers
       A UNHCR-supported documentation programme seeks to assure
       indigenous Sama Bajau people can access education, health care and
       housing in the Philippines.
       view story
     *
   Mexico. Salvadoran asylum-seeker family reunited in Saltillo
       Stories

Ground-breaking programme reunites families, reignites hope
       UNHCR's 'holistic' integration project helps refugees find jobs,
       education, homes and help towards naturalisation.
       view story
     *
   Italy. Humanitarian Corridors programme nominated for UNHCR's Nansen
       Award
       Stories

Life-saving programme offers safe path to Italy for refugees
       Humanitarian Corridors, a unique partnership set up by religious
       organizations, is the Europe regional winner for UNHCR's Nansen
       Refugee Award.
       view story

   Jordan. 'Mother of Syrians' nominated for UNHCR's Nansen Award

Jordanian volunteer helps Syrian refugees get back on their feet

   News and StoriesStories18 Sep 2019
   Ethiopia. Sharp increase in Somali refugees arriving in Ethiopia as
   drought and insecurity worsens

As drought compounds security woes, Somalis flee to Ethiopia

   News and StoriesStories20 Sep 2019

Eight refugees fighting for the planet

   20 Sep 2019

Help Rohingya refugees this monsoon season

Rain-filled monsoon winds have hit Bangladesh. Rohingya refugees are
struggling for survival.

   We urgently need your help during this emergency to train more refugees
   as first responders, secure shelter, insulation, relocate those most
   affected to safer land and more.


   Give now

$14

   can provide a Rohingya family with 5 sleeping mats
     __________________________________________________________________

$24

   can provide two liquefied petroleum gas refills to a Rohingya family
   for clean cooking and prevention of environmental damage
     __________________________________________________________________

$30

   can provide plastic tarpaulins to waterproof the roof of two families
   Fullscreen button

Around UNHCR

   Jordan. 'Mother of Syrians' nominated for UNHCR's Nansen Refugee Award

UNHCR names Nansen Refugee Award regional winners

   The every-day heroes from Africa, the Americas, Asia, Europe and the
   Middle East are being honoured for their outstanding humanitarian work.
   News and StoriesNews

A New Deal for Refugees

   The Global Compact on Refugees aims to improve the international
   response to new and existing refugee situations.

UNHCR's 2 Billion Kilometres to Safety campaign invites the public to step in
solidarity with refugees

   News and StoriesPress Releases
   Switzerland. Melissa Fleming's podcast interview with Sajjad Malik.

UNHCR podcast hears from the people who dedicate their lives to refugees

   Staff who have spent their careers in some of the world's most
   challenging places talk about what keeps them awake at night.

Cash assistance gives refugees the power of choice

   UNHCR is expanding cash-based assistance so that the millions of people
   that it serves can meet their needs in dignity and are protected.
